{
  "stem": "523.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were in [NON-ENGLISH], in Siberia, all over the places.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then after the war, they came to Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "From Poland they came to Germany, to the-- to the camps, for the refugee camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my husband came to Israel in 1948.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He came as a volunteer to fight in the army at that time, to independence of Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he was fighting in the mountains of Jerusalem, practically, with bare hands.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So-- that's-- that's how we met in '53.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's going to be-- in June it's going to be 16 years since we live in Toronto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes-- yes, all three children are married.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Henry has two sons.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His wife, Rebecca, and their two sons, David and Joshua.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my older one, David, is eight and a half years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I was deported, I was nine years old, only six months older than my older grandson.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I look at this little boy, he's protected as a child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the thought that this pure-- this innocent little boy could have been me, and lived at that time, it's so scary that this child-- I hope and pray that those children will never, ever know what me, as a child, ever, ever knew, especially now, denial of the Holocaust, neo-Nazis.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What is going on?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Give them, God forbid, an opportunity, they're going to do the same thing to our children, our grandchildren-- what the Hitlerites of yesteryear did to us, and maybe even worse.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After all, they have already lessons from those Hitlers and Eichmanns and the-- and all-- and the Himmlers, and the Mengeles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They will do even much more because they have their role models.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
